	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Her name is Oppia in Livy, Opimia in Dion. Hal., (Op)illia in Liv. Per. 2, Popillia in Oros. 2.8.13; Pompilia in Euseb. and Jerome Chr. ad ann. 486 B.C., 1.108f. ed.Helm, and Syncell. 483.7. See Klose, 34, no. 1; Münzer, Philologus 92(1937-38)211f." .
